news.title: Ajmera Realty & Infra's profit up 49% to Rs 31.43 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 196.15 crore in the April-June period of this fiscal from Rs 117.57 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Unitech reports net loss of Rs 1,206 crore in Q1FY25
news.para: Total income declined to Rs 84.04 crore in the April-June quarter of this fiscal from Rs 91.09 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.Unitech reports net loss of  Rs 1,206 crore in Q1FY25

news.title: Incuspaze leases four lakh sq ft office space in Noida from Bhutani Infra
news.para: Sanjay Chatrath, Managing Partner, Incuspaze, said, "Our recent expansions, including significant leases in Gurgaon, Bangalore, Mumbai, Pune, Jaipur and Lucknow, highlight our dedication to meeting the rising demand for flexible workspaces across the nation."

news.title: Grihum Housing Finance's net profit up 77% to Rs 46 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: “Our organisation now serves more than 80,000 customers. The Company is proactively aligned with regulators and financial institutions, and we have registered stable growth”, said Manish Jaiswal, Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer of Grihum Housing Finance Limited.

news.title: Ireland: IRES to pursure growth, sell less efficient units
news.para: Ireland's largest private residential landlord announced the review in January and said it would consider a potential sale or merger, asset disposals and new strategic initiatives, along with a review of its status as a listed REIT.

news.title: RBI keeps repo rate unchanged at 6.5%
news.para: Four out of the six members of MPC voted in favour of the rate decision. The panel, whose four-year term ends in October, also decided to retain a policy stance at "withdrawal of accommodation" to aid MPC's focus on bringing inflation towards its 4 per cent target.

news.title: South Korea to boost supply in the real estate market in bid to curb price rises
news.para: The real estate market snapped a six-month run of declines in June, as prices in the capital Seoul jumped by the most in 2-1/2 years, raising concerns among policymakers of a spike in household debt in what is already one of the world's most-indebted countries.

news.title: Tender released for TIDEL park construction in Madurai
news.para: According to the tender, the project will include a ground floor, 12 additional floors and a terrace, along with civil construction, interior finishing work, and other allied development tasks.

news.title: Varanasi: VDA issues dos & don'ts for old buildings in need of repair
news.para: VDA initiated the move after two dilapidated buildings collapsed in the Pancho Pandva area near Kashi Vishwanath Dham on Tuesday, claiming life of one woman. Eight persons, including a woman constable, suffered injuries in the incident.

news.title: Why Delhi's response to PM-UDAY has remained lukewarm
news.para: Responding to questions raised by South Delhi MP Ramvir Singh Bidhuri in Parliament, the Union housing and urban affairs minister said on July 25 that of the 1,22,729 applications received under PM-UDAY, only 23,811 were granted ownership rights, the highest being in Najafgarh, Nangloi, Burari and Kakrola.

news.title: HD-BRTS to develop transit-oriented projects in Hubballi
news.para: HD-BRTS general manager R Gudaraddi told STOI that TOD integrates land use and transport planning and aims to develop planned sustainable urban growth centres, having walkable and livable communes with high density mixed land use. “Citizens will be given an opportunity to access open green and public spaces while efficiently utilizing the transit facilities,” he official said.

news.title: Mahindra Group companies run into 'brand' tax
news.para: Mahindra & Mahindra received a notice from the GST office regarding the use of the 'Mahindra' brand name by group companies, questioning why GST wasn't paid for the service between 2017-23.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT posts profit of Rs 37.35 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Brookfield India REIT' adjusted net operating income (NOI) grew by 94% year-on-year from Rs 2,453 million in Q1 FY24 and operating lease rentals grew by 99% year-on-year from Rs 2,113 million in Q1 FY24.

news.title: NatWest Group leases 3.7 lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: The UK banking group said it has leased a new office in Bengaluru with a facility spanning 370,000 sq. ft. over 11 floors, to expand its engineering and innovation hub.

news.title: As many as 50,258 real estate cases pending in consumer courts: Government data
news.para: As per the data, there have been 2,44,813 cases filed in consumer courts at national, state and district levels. Out of that 1,94,555 cases have been disposed and 50,258 cases are pending as on July 31, 2024.

news.title: The Phoenix Mills acquires 9.03 acres land in Coimbatore for Rs 370.17 crore
news.para: Shishir Shrivastava, managing director of The Phoenix Mills said, "We are pleased to announce our acquisition in Coimbatore for a greenfield retail development project."

news.title: NITCO sells four-acre Mumbai plot to Runwal for Rs 232 crore
news.para: The developer is planning to invest Rs 1,500 crore including the land cost to develop a premium residential project on the land parcel.

news.title: Asian Granito India posts profit of Rs 35.36 lakh in Q1 FY25
news.para: Asian Granito India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 343.66 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 0.98 per cent from Rs 340.31 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ajmera Realty issues additional 2% equity shares to its existing shareholders upon de-merger
news.para: The de-merger was approved by NCLT on the July 4, 2024. As per the scheme of arrangement, ARIIL has allotted one equity share with the face value of Rs 10 each against every 50 shares held to its equity shareholders.

news.title: Sobha signs joint develop agreement to construct residential project in Gurugram
news.para: According to the documents accessed through CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm, the deal got registered on July 12 and Sobha has paid Rs 4.3 crore stamp duty for the transaction.
